In order to discuss the influence of foam density on the properties of nanocomposite foams, the influence of solid matrix properties is excluded by normalizing the Young’s modulus (<i>E</i>foam
                           ) and collapse strength (<i>σ</i>cl
                           ) of the polymer foams by the Young’s modulus (<i>E</i>solid
                           ) and compressive strength (<i>σ</i>solid
                           ) of the corresponding solid samples. The normalized values are termed the relative modulus (<i>E</i>r
                            = <i>E</i>foam
                           /<i>E</i>solid
                           ) and the relative strength (<i>σ</i>r
                            = <i>σ</i>cl
                           /<i>σ</i>solid
                           ).
